  "script": "A giraffe is loose? In Real County, Texas, a giraffe named Gracie strolled right off a ranch — and now authorities are asking the public to help find a 14-foot animal that is somehow hiding in plain sight. Think about how absurd that search is. You can't exactly tuck a giraffe behind a bush. Officials are warning people: do not chase her, do not corner her, just call it in if you spot that long neck over the treeline. A spooked giraffe can run 30 miles an hour and kick hard enough to kill a lion. So somewhere in the Texas hill country, the tallest fugitive alive is on the run. How do you even lose a giraffe in the first place?",
